sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K891004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Probe coding for the Omega Fragment of beta galactosidase
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The following part consists of a constitutive promoter plus RBS (BBa_J61100), which codes for the protein Streptavidin linked to the omega fragment of Beta Galactosidase via Linker (BBa_J176040).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Abhinav Markus
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: All parts were used from the Registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Works only if bounded with its alpha compliment.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K283010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for streptavidin which binds with biotin. The streptavidin coding region does not contain any rbs nor terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Shi Lei

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PLflex
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Flexible linker peptide made of two GGGGS repeats
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Karmella Haynes

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K891003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: LacZ- omega fragment. Binds to the alpha fragment of LacZ and becomes a workable unit.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Abhinav Markus
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Isolated the fragment from the PSV plasmid from promega.
